Anti-aliased polyphase k=5 (L=600, pk_k5_filt) at WIDE channels (96/192/384, ~490k params). 31-tap FIR Hamming low-pass at Nyquist=100 Hz, applied with filtfilt for zero phase, BEFORE taking each phase. RF=125 sub-samples = 625 raw-ms. KEY EXPERIMENT: combines two fixes against the apr25 k=5 collapse (+0.087) — (a) anti-aliasing, (b) restored capacity. Cleanest comparison is to apr26_multiseed_k5_wide which had wide channels but unfiltered data (+0.132). Recovery toward k=2 territory (+0.34) → aliasing was the dominant cause; staying near +0.13 → DMT signal genuinely needs content above 100 Hz.